name: 3-amino-1-(4-chlorophenyl)-1h-pyrazole
Reason: 3-amino-1-(4-chlorophenyl)-1H-pyrazole has a pyrazole ring, which is known to increase the melting point due to the presence of a nitrogen atom. The chlorine atom also increases the melting point due to the increased electronegativity and polarizability. The 4-chlorophenyl group also increases the melting point due to the increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces. The amino group decreases the melting point due to the increased hydrogen bonding capabilities. The net effect of these functional groups is an increase in the melting point.
